  export const MS_PER_SECOND = 1000;
  export const SECONDS_PER_MINUTE = 60;
  export const MINUTES_PER_HOUR = 60;
  export const HOURS_PER_DAY = 24;
Then import from `shared/constants/time` in admin, payments, and store. The store's cartCookiePersistence.ts uses these as file-local consts — import from shared instead.

Extract to a root-level shared config file, e.g. config/nextSecurityHeaders.ts:
  export const securityHeaders = [...];
Then import in each next.config.ts:
  import { securityHeaders } from '../../config/nextSecurityHeaders';
This is low risk since config/ already exists at the repo root (config/app-links.json).
